# =============================================================================
# Docker Build Context Exclusions — apps/web
# =============================================================================
# Keep build context small and fast; prevent stale build artifacts from being
# COPY'd into the image (the shard-54 cache trap: a stale .next/ shipped in
# prod because Dockerfile does `COPY . .` after `npm ci`, so anything present
# on the host got layered in AFTER `npm run build` wrote its own .next).
# =============================================================================

# Git
.git
.gitignore

# Dependencies — Dockerfile runs `npm ci` itself
node_modules
.pnp
.pnp.js

# Next.js build output — MUST be rebuilt inside the container, never shipped
# from host. Leaving this out of .dockerignore caused stale JS chunks in prod.
.next
out

# Production build
build
dist

# Test artifacts (Playwright/Vitest)
test-results
playwright-report
.auth-state.json
coverage
.nyc_output

# TypeScript incremental build info
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Local env files — NEVER include secrets in image
.env
.env.*
*.local

# Vercel local state
.vercel

# IDE / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Docs (not needed at runtime)
*.md
README*

# Docker files themselves don't need to be in the build context
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore
